xmlDB is an php file which gives you the possibility to create a
small xml Database.
Most of the xmlDB commands are based an the php mysql class, so 
it is easy to learn.

The code is commented and simple written so its easy to understand

Today Nico started the first Extended Version of xmlDB, called xmlDB_SQL
it will give you a xml_query($query) command which can parse an SQL Query 
string to xmlDB functions.

Some will say this should be in the main xmlDB file, but we discussed 
this and our conclusion was to keep xmlDB als small as possible with
no function not truly needed.(so it can be used for mobile devices without
performance loss)

If you have any Ideas to Extend xmlDB or think there is a 
core function missing feel free to write it!